++ Copy On Write

Copy on Write means that upon a write, instead of modifying the original - a copy is created which is modified instead. This preserves the original while allowing a mofification to be present.
    * Copy on Write can be used as a crude [Backup] solution.
    * MultipleManagement 
    * Used for ChangePreserving
    * AccidentSafety

might be a good idea on files too, not just config (checkbox)